Rasheed Bisiriyu The 2020 Geneva International Motor Show was around the corner when coronavirus struck in Wuhan, China and has since spread to many countries across the globe. Like many international events fixed for this period, the famous motor show has been cancelled. But the concerns surrounding the COVID-19 outbreak has only denied the new cars enthusiasts the physical assessment of the latest hi-tech automobiles. Pictures of many new supercars and concepts already arranged for unveiling at the event have surfaced online. Some of these new cars and concepts for display at the event in Switzerland can now be found in the Virtual Geneva Motor Show Gallery. Many auto reviewers who have seen the list of vehicles says it is a combination of over-the-top supercars and forward thinking electric vehicles. Autoblog.com says, “Even without a show, these cars stood out.” Top on the list are Hyundai Prophesy, Aston Martin V12 Speedster, Volkswagen ID.4, Alfa Romeo Giulia Quadrifoglio GTA and Koenigsegg Gemera. Copyright PUNCH.
